      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While inflammation is a major source of pain, pushing through severe pain without knowing the underlying issue is dangerous. If you are unable to put *any* weight on it now, waiting to walk on it in 48 hours could be very problematic. Ibuprofen can help manage pain, but it won't correct a structural injury, so please consider seeing a professional to rule out a bad break before you try to \"tough it out.\"",
